In user management it would help if the Group dropdown had "None" in addition to "Any". This would help finding users who have been removed from all groups (for cleanup, or re-adding, for example).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-7558].
  {panel}

Need to write a doc that answer a query such as:

i want to internationalize my plugin. Actually i have a properties-file which contains the english Strings of the plugin. Now i will support another language. 
So what i have to do? I think  i need another properties-file for the other language. But how to bind in?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-7553].
  {panel}

We have just realized that some of the problems that developers are having with not being able to find issues is due to their looking for text that exists in the worklogs but not anywhere else in the issue. Turns out the search doesn't look in the worklog text ... this is a bad thing. I looked at every issue here that the search found using the word worklog and none of those mentioned this problem.

