{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-7498].
  {panel}

When viewing a workflow (ViewWorkflowSteps.jspa), one sees all the steps and transitions for a workflow, *except* the initial 'Create issue' transition.  This is a pity, because the 'Create issue' transition is a commonly used, and its omission leads people to think that it cannot be edited.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-7483].
  {panel}

JIRA's CVS parser ignores the initial commit in a module, as this is usually from an 'import' command, and generally doesn't contain anything interesting (this is a rationalization for a technical limitation, really).  In some circumstances (eg. using vendor branches to port changes), the initial commit does contain useful information, and so should be parsed.

If you do a quicksearch with an issue key for an issue that doesnt exist, you should end up at the issuenotfound.jsp view.. but instead we get an error.

Occasionally, we also get an error about the error page itself (but I think this may just be a distraction):
Error page exception
The server cannot use the error page specified for your application to handle the Original Exception printed below. Please see the Error Page Exception below for a description of the problem with the specified error page.

Which suggests it isnt going to the 500 page....
But sometimes it does go to the 500 page.... I dont know whats happenning there..

I am working on finding out what exactly is causing this, but here are the stacktraces (they are quite long)


